page.title: 15FLITWICK WOOD
page.content: FLITWICK WOOD DATES FROM PRE-NORMAN TIMES.THE POSITION OF FLITWICK WOOD IS:020 347(ON THE BEDFORD AND LUTON O.S MAP)FLITWICK WOOD IS A DECIDUOUS BLACK POPLAR PLANTATION.THE SOIL IS MOSTLY SANDY LOAM. {TREES: IN FLITWICK WOOD THERE ARE SEVERAL VARIETIES OF TREES.THERE ARE LARGE NUMBERS OF:BLACK POPLARS, SYCAMORE, OAK,ASH. THE NOT SO COMMON ONES ARE :PINE, SWEET CHESTNUT,ELM,BIRCH,BEECH. {SHRUBS: THERE ARE LARGE NUMBERS OF: BLACKTHORN,ELDER,HAZEL,HAWTHORN. THE NOT SO COMMON ONES ARE:HOLLY, HONEY-SUCKLE,DOGROSE,BROOM,BLACKBERRY. {FLOWERING PLANTS: THERE ARE LARGE NUMBERS OF:CLOVER, THISTLE,DOCK,GOOZEGRASS,BUTTERCUPS, BLUEBELL,NETTLES AND WILD GARLIC.
